# still read as smooth colored patches glued on a flat plane, not actual rough rock, per direct
# feedback with a screenshot). This version gives every wall/ceiling cell an actual depth of 0, 1 or
# 2 blocks (not just a different material at the same flat depth), so the surface itself is jagged --
# some cells stay flush, some poke out 1 block, some poke out 2, mixed with no visible pattern.
# Skips cells already inside a choke-point bulge or low-ceiling pocket (already deeper than this),
